01:11:50.448 --> 01:11:53.788
We estimate climate and environment to be a little more than 6% of the CEO's

1261
01:11:53.808 --> 01:11:56.328
responsibilities. To suggest that there will still be a

1262
01:11:57.308 --> 01:11:59.528
Secretary for the Environment is confusing at best.

1263
01:12:01.008 --> 01:12:04.498
Critically, the merger will submerge decisions of value judgments,

1264
01:12:04.708 --> 01:12:07.508
trade-offs between safe long-term environments and climate,

1265
01:12:08.528 --> 01:12:10.848
and largely short-term development considerations.

1266
01:12:11.928 --> 01:12:15.408
Maintaining transparency, openness, and a sense of public ownership in

1267
01:12:15.468 --> 01:12:17.268
environmental policy is worth a great deal.

1268
01:12:18.088 --> 01:12:21.708
Without a dedicated point of contact, public participation trust will likely

1269
01:12:21.828 --> 01:12:22.128
