01:12:39.808 --> 01:12:43.608
To conclude, the Nelson Tasman Climate Forum strongly opposes the

1276
01:12:43.648 --> 01:12:47.468
disestablishment of the Ministry for the Environment for reasons of

1277
01:12:47.548 --> 01:12:51.228
transparency, accountability, and its role for restoring our climate,

1278
01:12:51.728 --> 01:12:54.988
protecting nature to tire, and protecting future generations.

1279
01:12:56.308 --> 01:12:56.688
However,

1280
01:12:57.548 --> 01:13:01.388
if the committee is of a mind to recommend the bill proceed, and in a departure

1281
01:13:01.448 --> 01:13:02.688
from our written submission,

1282
01:13:03.788 --> 01:13:07.418
we recommend broadly following the Environmental Law Initiative

1283
01:13:07.468 --> 01:13:11.384
proposalTo establish the Secretary for the Environment as Deputy

1284
01:13:11.484 --> 01:13:15.004
Chief Executive of the new ministry with an exclusive mandate

1285
01:13:15.484 --> 01:13:19.434
and sufficient resources for its climate and environment responsibilities,

1286
01:13:20.424 --> 01:13:23.604
and to provide direction that the new ministry must

1287
01:13:23.624 --> 01:13:27.104
prioritize our national climate obligations and environmental

