1309
01:14:42.244 --> 01:14:44.084
us through your submission. So thank you.

1310
01:14:45.244 --> 01:14:49.024
Thanks, Madam Chair. Look, there's no right way to arrange government

1311
01:14:49.104 --> 01:14:51.924
departments, so anything can be made to work.

1312
01:14:52.344 --> 01:14:55.044
And if you want to get rid of the Ministry for the Environment, this is, from a

1313
01:14:55.104 --> 01:14:58.264
legal point of view, an elegant way. So that's good.

1314
01:14:58.944 --> 01:15:02.564
However, in my view, a separate ministry remains the best

1315
01:15:02.624 --> 01:15:06.504
way to ensure that environmental problems are properly addressed.

1316
01:15:07.304 --> 01:15:11.284
Unlike domains such as transport, housing or infrastructure, where there are

1317
01:15:11.364 --> 01:15:15.294
numerous private and public owners, operators and

1318
01:15:15.364 --> 01:15:19.344
interest groups, the environment doesn't have anyone that can

1319
01:15:19.384 --> 01:15:20.624
claim to own it.

1320
01:15:21.484 --> 01:15:24.644
All of us are dependent on the environment of which we're a part.

1321
01:15:25.404 --> 01:15:28.964
Now, in my view, it makes sense to have an agency whose job it is to

1322
01:15:29.004 --> 01:15:29.504
ensure

1323
01:15:30.304 --> 01:15:33.924
that the consequences for the environment of all our other policy interventions are

1324
01:15:33.964 --> 01:15:34.984
properly understood.

1325
01:15:36.064 --> 01:15:39.784
If we can justify a separate ministry for regulation,

1326
01:15:40.344 --> 01:15:43.804
we can certainly justify a separate ministry for the environment.

1327
01:15:44.484 --> 01:15:48.304
Now, as the officer of Parliament charged with keeping under review

1328
01:15:48.804 --> 01:15:52.244
the system of processes and agencies that make up our

1329
01:15:52.264 --> 01:15:55.444
environmental management system, my advice to

1330
01:15:55.524 --> 01:15:59.404
you is that this change is unlikely to help

1331
01:15:59.494 --> 01:16:02.234
the environment, and I want to underline three points briefly.

1332
01:16:02.444 --> 01:16:02.813
First,

1333
01:16:03.824 --> 01:16:07.644
bundling these agencies together undermines an important principle of

1334
01:16:07.684 --> 01:16:10.644
public sector advice, and that is the need for

1335
01:16:10.704 --> 01:16:11.854
contestability

1336
01:16:12.664 --> 01:16:16.424
so that elected officials, in other words, ministers, not public

1337
01:16:16.504 --> 01:16:20.364
servants, can confront and make the big trade-offs.

1338
01:16:21.284 --> 01:16:25.004
There's a real risk with a mega ministry that trade-offs will be resolved

1339
01:16:25.084 --> 01:16:29.044
within the organization, and that the differences will not

1340
01:16:29.144 --> 01:16:32.604
be aired with ministers, where accountability for those trade-offs

1341
01:16:32.844 --> 01:16:34.364
should rightly sit.

1342
01:16:35.384 --> 01:16:38.924
Now, neither the previous nor the current government have made a convincing case,

1343
01:16:38.984 --> 01:16:42.044
in my view, that to reform the RMA you need two acts.

1344
01:16:42.104 --> 01:16:45.404
But if you are all agreed that that's the right approach, then

1345
01:16:45.984 --> 01:16:49.604
surely it would make sense to have different ministries responsible

1346
01:16:49.704 --> 01:16:53.524
for the two different acts to ensure that the trade-offs between

1347
01:16:53.564 --> 01:16:55.384
them are properly presented.

1348
01:16:56.544 --> 01:17:00.104
Frankly, I don't have a lot of confidence in large, internal,

1349
01:17:00.464 --> 01:17:02.664
bureaucratic trade-off exercises.

1350
01:17:03.574 --> 01:17:07.484
A Ministry for the Environment overseeing a Natural Environment Act

1351
01:17:08.164 --> 01:17:11.664
would better ensure free and frank advice than a mega ministry

1352
01:17:12.204 --> 01:17:16.164
trying to reach a compromise it hopes all of its ministers can swallow.

1353
01:17:16.924 --> 01:17:20.884
There's also a transparency point that you as a select committee should seek advice

1354
01:17:20.984 --> 01:17:21.164
on.

1355
01:17:21.964 --> 01:17:25.264
Right now, the Ministry for the Environment has two appropriations, one for

1356
01:17:25.283 --> 01:17:28.843
environment, one for climate. You need to find out in this merged

1357
01:17:28.904 --> 01:17:32.584
ministry if there is going to be an appropriation for those

1358
01:17:32.624 --> 01:17:32.924
things.

1359
01:17:33.724 --> 01:17:37.424
With my EEE, which I bring to you once a year, my estimate of

1360
01:17:37.444 --> 01:17:41.264
environmental expenditure, I can tell you what's being spent on

1361
01:17:41.324 --> 01:17:43.004
those items from the budget.

1362
01:17:43.804 --> 01:17:47.784
I may not be able to do so anywhere near so easily if this is all just

1363
01:17:47.804 --> 01:17:51.384
put into a big blender and you can't see what's being spent

1364
01:17:52.044 --> 01:17:52.964
on the environment.

1365
01:17:53.984 --> 01:17:57.664
Okay, my second point. If you believe that a smaller

1366
01:17:57.704 --> 01:18:01.304
number of mega ministries is better, then you should at least be

1367
01:18:01.364 --> 01:18:04.704
prepared to consider merging MFE with MPI.

1368
01:18:05.404 --> 01:18:08.504
Now, that may shock some people, and it's not my first preference.

1369
01:18:09.084 --> 01:18:12.924
After all, many of our most pressing environmental problems are associated

1370
01:18:12.964 --> 01:18:16.664
with primary industries like water quality, greenhouse gas

1371
01:18:16.724 --> 01:18:20.604
emissions and erosion. So I suppose there could be a problem for free and

1372
01:18:20.624 --> 01:18:23.944
frank advice about those problems if you put those together.

1373
01:18:23.964 --> 01:18:27.864
But look at it another way. The current proposal is to create

1374
01:18:27.964 --> 01:18:31.844
a very urban-focused ministry. It seems to have been the

1375
